EC2= Elastic compute cloud= infrastructure as a service
consist out of:
  *Renting virtual machines
  *Storing data on virtual drives/EBS
  *Distributing load across machines/ELB
  *Scaling the services using an auto-scaling group/ASG
configuration possibilities:
  *OS
  *CPU
  *RAM
  *storage space options:
    *Network attached
      **EBS
      **EFS
    *Hardware
      *EC2 instance store
  *Network card: speed of the card, public ip address
  *Firewall rules: security groups
  *bootstrap script: runs scripts when the machine starts
    **used for installing updates, software,... => always in root user

for creating and EC2 instance:
1) go to ec2
2) got to instances
3) launch instances
4) give it a name(Linux Web Server)
5) choose which operating system (AWS linux)
6) create a key pair if you wnat to login via console
  6.1) give it a name b.e. linux web server key pair
  6.2) choose RSA for encryption and .pem if you're machine is older than or equal to windows 10 otherwise use .ppk
  6.3) create a security group for the first one do the default
  6.4) because this is a web server markdown http traffic
  6.5) and because it's a web server you want to set user data so that it creates it's the first time when launching it

